  "title": "Bounded on a Set",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $A \\subseteq \\mathbb{R}$ and $f \\colon A \\to \\mathbb{R}$. The function $f$ is bounded on $A$ if and only if there exists a constant $M>0$ such that $|f(x)| \\le M$ for every $x \\in A$.",
